The code statements that lead to the bug are:
```java
if (cache) {
    session.setAuthType(authType);
    session.setPrincipal(principal);
}
```
Reason:
The logic incorrectly allows the principal to be cached in the session even when the `cache` flag is set to false, leading to potential security issues by persisting stale or incorrect principal information across sessions.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```java
if (session != null) {
    if (cache) {
        session.setAuthType(authType);
        session.setPrincipal(principal);
    } else {
        if (username != null) {
            session.setNote(Constants.SESS_USERNAME_NOTE, username);
        } else {
            session.removeNote(Constants.SESS_USERNAME_NOTE);
        }
        if (password != null) {
            session.setNote(Constants.SESS_PASSWORD_NOTE, password);
        } else {
            session.removeNote(Constants.SESS_PASSWORD_NOTE);
        }
    }
}
```
Reason:
The patch refactors the conditional logic to ensure that the principal is only cached in the session if the `cache` flag is true, preventing incorrect authentication states and ensuring that the session does not retain stale principal information when caching is disabled.

